        <section>
            <draft-comment author="LAWSONZ">Here's where I can put in a note to self or a question
                to developers.</draft-comment>
            <p>In general, a reference topic is used for things you look up. If you want to put it
                in a table, it probably should be a reference topic.</p>
            <p>Reference topics can contain:</p>
            <dl>
                <dlentry>
                    <dt><xmlelement>section</xmlelement></dt>
                    <dd>Generic text space.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry>
                    <dt><xmlelement>example</xmlelement></dt>
                    <dd>Generic text but the intention is to hold some sort of example.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry>
                    <dt><xmlelement>properties</xmlelement></dt>
                    <dd>A special list/table for properties and definitions.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry>
                    <dt><xmlelement>refsyn</xmlelement></dt>
                    <dd>Syntax reference. Great for APIs.</dd>
                </dlentry>
            </dl>
            <dl>
                <dlentry>
                    <dt><xmlelement>simpletable</xmlelement> or <xmlelement>table</xmlelement></dt>
                    <dd>You can have a table. </dd>
                </dlentry>
            </dl>
        </section>
    </refbody>
